40|$|We {{consider}} {{two related}} but often-unlinked questions concerning <b>airport</b> <b>policy.</b> Should Canadian airports {{be subject to}} direct government regulation and how is this question informed by the role airports play in determining airline competition? We consider these questions {{in light of the}} recent history of devolution for Canadian airports under the National <b>Airport</b> <b>Policy,</b> and the current review of Canada’s Transportation Act by the Federal Government. We conclude that Canadian <b>airport</b> <b>policy</b> requires a series of substantial changes, the cumulative effects of which are required to address efficiency and airline competition issues. More generally we argue that the role of airports in fostering domestic airline competition strengthens the arguments against direct (pricecap) regulation. Keywords: JEL Classifications...|$|E
