50|$|Canada's National Airport System (NAS) {{was defined}} in the National <b>Airports</b> <b>Policy</b> {{published}} in 1994. It was intended to include all airports with an annual traffic of 200,000 passengers or more, as well as airports serving the national, provincial and territorial capitals.|$|R
